  <title>Course Topics</title>
  <p component="4083">
    This course can be divided into two parts.
    In the first, we cover the definitions and examples of groups, subgroups, quotient groups, homomorphisms, and important theorems about the structure of certain groups.
    <!-- such as Sylowâ€™s Theorem and the Fundamental Theorem of Finitely Generated Abelian Groups.-->
    In the second, we encounter basic definitions and examples of rings, subrings, ideals, quotients of rings, domains, fields, homomorphisms, and other topics as time permits.
  </p>
